Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

This looks good.  The only thing I noticed in testing is that I got a foreign key constraint that blocked purging the images table, but that was mostly because of the nature of my test data.  What happened was that all my stuff had deleted_at within the same day, and I used --max_rows so I didn't purge all of it.  It just so happened that when I later tested the purge_images_table call, some image_properties and image_locations were hanging around that prevented the row in the images table from being purged.  I think the best way to deal with this is to mention it in the documentation, namely, that if you don't run the "regular" purge first, you're likely to get and IntegrityError when you purge the images table.  I don't think it's a problem because the intended use is that an operator will be regularly "regular" purging, and at some point may need to purge some really old stuff out of the images table.  Under that scenario, this error won't occur.
